eval(ez_write_tag([[468,60],'constructionreviewonline_com-medrectangle-3','ezslot_1',114,'0','0']));According to the Council of Tall Buildings and Urban Habitat, a steel “steel skyscraper” is one whose main construction vertical and lateral structural elements, as well as floor systems, are constructed from steel. The idea of steel skyscrapers was first fronted by Fazlur Khan, a vibrant young engineer of Bengali descent. Although there are a number of incredible steel structures scattered around the world, these kinds of buildings are a phenomenon in their own right, relying solely on the brazen strength of steel for structural integrity. Below we look at the top 10 tallest steel buildings in the world.   eval(ez_write_tag([[300,250],'constructionreviewonline_com-medrectangle-4','ezslot_0',115,'0','0']));Also called the Sears Tower, Willis Tower was completed in 1974 having been constructed for just three years. The building was erected at a time when America was facing a building. Sears Tower stands 442m high and is the tallest steel building in the world. The building was constructed using Bundled Tube structural engineering principles and its strength comes from a combination of nine main structures arranged in a three by three grid that make up the complex. Willis Tower has 101 floors.   The Empire State Building is one of the world’s most iconic buildings. The building is easily recognizable thanks to its thrusting pinnacle and broad, sprawling base. The building was completed in 1931 and was the tallest building in the world for more than 40 years. The 381 structure took 13months to construct. Its construction involved a lot of planning. During construction, steel girders were ordered to length and arrived on site ready to go and each girder was marked with where it would be placed in the framework.   Standing 88 storeys high, the Aon Center in Chicago is the third tallest steel building in the world. The 346m building is the third tallest in Chicago and uses a tubular steel frame to provide it with weather and earthquake resisting properties. The steel structure is the headquarters of insurance broker Aon.   The Center is a monumental steel building located in Hong Kong’s central business district. The 346m-tall building is one of the few steel skyscrapers in Hong Kong. The building is not reinforced with concrete, which saw its construction completed in just three years.   Another one from Chicago.  The 344m-tall John Hancock Centre has a trussed tube structural engineering design which is evident on the building’s exterior. The building was designed by the same company who built the World Trade Centres and was completed in 1965.   The Minsheng Bank Building is located in Wuhan, China, and stands 68 floors or 331m high. The building is taller than World Trade Centre III by just a meter and mainly composed of steel, and rests on a multi-story podium structure.   The China World Trade Centre III is a steel skyscraper located in the central business district of Beijing. Construction of the building started in 2007 and was completed in 2010. The building has a close resemblance to the World Trade Centers destroyed in the 9/11 attack, hence the name.   The Chrysler Building was completed in 1930 and became the tallest building in the world at the time, toppling the Eiffel Tower as the tallest building in the world. The 319m-facility was the first human-made structure to stand taller than 1,000 feet. <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-119420" src=https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-New-York-Times-Tower-259x320.jpg alt width=259 height=320 srcset="https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-New-York-Times-Tower-259x320.jpg 259w, https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-New-York-Times-Tower-517x640.jpg 517w, https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-New-York-Times-Tower-768x950.jpg 768w, https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-New-York-Times-Tower-324x400.jpg 324w, https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-New-York-Times-Tower-696x861.jpg 696w, https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-New-York-Times-Tower-339x420.jpg 339w, https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-New-York-Times-Tower.jpg 800w" sizes="(max-width: 259px) 100vw, 259px"> The New York Times Tower was completed in 2007 after a four year construction period and is one of the tallest steel buildings globally.  The 319m tall building is the headquarters of the New York Times and has a variety of green energy features including double-skin curtain walls, automated louver shading systems, a dimmable lighting system, an underfloor air distribution system, and cogeneration. <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-119421" src=https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-US-Bank-Tower-212x320.jpg alt width=212 height=320 srcset="https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-US-Bank-Tower-212x320.jpg 212w, https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-US-Bank-Tower-425x640.jpg 425w, https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-US-Bank-Tower-768x1157.jpg 768w, https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-US-Bank-Tower-696x1048.jpg 696w, https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-US-Bank-Tower-279x420.jpg 279w, https://constructionreviewonline.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/The-US-Bank-Tower.jpg 863w" sizes="(max-width: 212px) 100vw, 212px"> It is evident that the US dominates the list of the tallest steel buildings in the world. The US Bank Tower is the tallest building in California and one of the most iconic structures in Los Angeles skylines. The building has 73 storeys and stands 310 meters high.